## 1. Component Style Structure
```css
/* 1. Component Namespace */
.your-plugin-component {
    /* Base component styles */
}

/* 2. Component States */
.your-plugin-component--active {
    /* Active state styles */
}

/* 3. Component Children */
.your-plugin-component__child {
    /* Child element styles */
}
```

## 2. WordPress Core Integration
```css
/* 1. Match WordPress Admin Colors */
.your-plugin-component {
    --wp-admin-theme-color: #2271b1;
    --wp-admin-theme-color-darker-10: #185a9d;
    --wp-admin-theme-color-darker-20: #124f89;
}

/* 2. Use WordPress Admin Patterns */
.your-plugin-card {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #c3c4c7;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 1px rgba(0,0,0,.04);
}
```

## 3. Component Specificity Rules
```css
/* 1. Use Classes Over IDs */
/* CORRECT */
.your-plugin-status { }

/* INCORRECT */
#your-plugin-status { }

/* 2. Avoid Deep Nesting */
/* CORRECT */
.your-plugin-card__header { }

/* INCORRECT */
.your-plugin-card .card-inner .header { }
```

## 4. Responsive Implementation
```css
/* 1. Use WordPress Breakpoints */
@media screen and (max-width: 782px) {
    .your-plugin-component {
        /* Tablet styles */
    }
}

@media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
    .your-plugin-component {
        /* Mobile styles */
    }
}
```

## 5. State Management
```css
/* 1. Loading States */
.your-plugin-component--loading {
    opacity: 0.7;
    pointer-events: none;
}

/* 2. Error States */
.your-plugin-component--error {
    border-color: #d63638;
}

/* 3. Success States */
.your-plugin-component--success {
    border-color: #00a32a;
}
```